44c8-ae3c-98dcb067d5f9","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["<em>Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been replaced by another product. You can still read our original review below, but Top Ten Reviews is no longer updating this product’s information.</em>","The Olympus VN-6000 is a simple <a href=\"/best-digital-voice-recorders\">digital voice recorder</a>. It&#39;s perfect for recording audio memos or notes, simple reminders, dictation or for students&#39; needs in any class, lecture or seminar. It isn&#39;t on the cutting edge of technology, but its practicality is undeniable.","The beauty of the Olympus VN-6000 is its simplicity. It has fewer features and functions than the other voice recorders on our list. It&#39;s easy to use, and that&#39;s always a benefit. However, this model lacks a USB connection, has no memory card slot or other means of transferring recording tracks to  a computer to edit or replay them. If that&#39;s a feature you need, this recorder is not for you.","Its 1GB of storage is sufficient for most recording needs. It has voice activation to ensure it records only when someone is speaking. This feature preserves memory and battery life. The device has a maximum of 604 hours of recording time, which is more than most of the other products on our lineup, that provides ample space for students, professionals or at-home use.","The Olympus VN-6000 features track marking, or indexing, to designate specific sections of a recording to easily return to and replay them. It has variable-speed playback that lets you listen to audio 50 percent faster or 25 percent slower than the normal speed. This expedites listening to and managing tracks, helping you save valuable time.","The device has a standard earphone jack and four recording folders. Each folder holds 100 files, which can be transferred easily between folders and erased when you no longer need them. The folders make it easy to efficiently manage all your audio files. The recorder has a timer that can be set to start and end recording at certain times and an alarm for reminders or to wake you up.","There are three options for obtaining support for this digital voice recorder. These include standard online FAQs, and email and phone support. Brochures and instruction manuals are also available on the Olympus website.","Olympus customer service representatives answer email queries the same day, sometimes within a couple of hours. You may call Olympus at the numbers listed on its website from 9 a.m. to 9 p.m., Eastern Standard Time, Monday through Friday.","Founded in 1919 and best known for its production of cameras beginning in the 1930s, Olympus now produces some of the best digital cameras in the world. The Japanese company also is a leader in audio products. The company offers dozens of voice recorders that vary in quality and available features. In addition, Olympus is a leader in the production of clinical and research equipment, including microscopes, gastro-intestinal endoscopes, ultrasound devices and other medical products."]},"id":"31b6d316-a8db-410a-8dd6-6d5d05dc1464","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"ad04c32b-a5b5-4f0e-af2c-812c210bd03b","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Sometimes simpler is better. That&#39;s the case with the easy-to-navigate Olympus VN-6000 voice recorder. It has no USB or other connection to transfer files from it to your computer. This device lets you record reminders, memos, university lectures, notes and more, and replay them at your convenience. Its handheld design and smooth interface make it a product that anyone of almost any age can use."]},"id":"ebee205e-65ec-4d1c-9bc0-8d775d290079","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_54196","url":"/olympus-vn-6000-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"jeph-preece","url":"/author/jeph-preece","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Jeph Preece","dateModified":"2019-04-17T2